/*Okay, FUTURE COS AND ANYONE ELSE READING THIS: See how all those lines up there in the boot stuff end with \e? DON'T DO THAT HERE; IT'S ALREADY IN THE CLOSING
DIALOGUE PRINT-OFF IN THE ACTUAL CODE. If you put one here by accident and there's another ghost on screen, he won't actually close when he reads it; he'll just
sit there like nothing happened because the \e is the 'end of dialogue' thing. Also, you don't have to put \w8's; I accounted for them as well.

For reference, here's what is tacked onto the end of his dialogue in bootend: "\w8\w8\-\e"*/

